SECTION 1 — FIX: form_errors not displaying in chat
==============================================================================
SYMPTOM: Backend sends {"type": "form_errors", "form_id": "...", "errors": {...}} 
but frontend only shows "⚠️ Form validation failed. Please correct the errors above." 
with no actual field-level errors visible.

DIAGNOSIS: In src/hooks/useChatStream.js, the form_errors SSE event handler sets 
formErrors on the message object. But FormRenderer.jsx either does not read 
formErrors or does not map them to individual field error displays.

FIX STEPS:

A. In src/hooks/useChatStream.js, find the form_errors case in the SSE event handler:

   The current handler sets formErrors on a message at msgIndex. Verify:
   - formErrors is being set as: { "project_id": "error text", "items.0.item_name": "error text" }
   - The message object at msgIndex is being mutated/replaced correctly
   - State update triggers a re-render (check if setMessages is called with a new array)

   If formErrors is being set but UI doesn't show it, the bug is in FormRenderer.jsx (go to B).
   If formErrors is not being set at all, fix the handler first.

B. In src/components/FormRenderer.jsx, find where individual fields are rendered.

   For EACH field, add inline error display below the input:
   
   - FormRenderer receives a `formErrors` prop (object: {fieldName: errorMessage})
   - After each field's input element, add:
   
     {formErrors?.[field.name] && (
       <p className="mt-1 text-xs text-red-400 flex items-center gap-1">
         <span>⚠</span>
         <span>{formErrors[field.name]}</span>
       </p>
     )}
   
   - For nested errors like "items.0.item_name", map them as:
     key = "items.0.item_name" → show below the field with name "item_name" 
     that is at index 0 in the items array. 
     If the form has table/array rows, each row's field should check 
     formErrors[`items.${rowIndex}.${field.name}`]
   
   - Apply error styling to the input itself when an error exists:
     Add to the input className: formErrors?.[field.name] ? 'border-red-500 ring-1 ring-red-500/20' : ''
   
   - The overall error banner ("⚠️ Form validation failed...") should REMAIN at 
     the top of the form but should only appear when Object.keys(formErrors).length > 0

C. In src/components/ChatOverlay.jsx (or wherever MessageBubble renders forms), 
   verify that when re-rendering a form message with formErrors set, the FormRenderer 
   is passed the updated formErrors prop. The form should NOT be re-mounted — 
   it should update in place preserving user's filled values.

D. IMPORTANT: After errors are shown, user fixes fields and resubmits. On new 
   submission, clear the formErrors state for that message so stale errors disappear. 
   In useChatStream.js submitForm(), before sending, clear formErrors on the 
   relevant message.

EXPECTED RESULT: User submits form with invalid project_id → backend returns 
form_errors → the project_id field shows red border + "Project 'yaq134e' not found" 
below it → item_name field shows "Item code 'rewqg435' not found in catalog" below it.

